@Date:	04-NOV-1964
@Time Duration:	10:00-11:00
@Situation:	A new child has appeared on the scene. His name is Diandra and he is three years old. The Smiths are taking him into their home and for a few months to see if the environment will improve his rate of development. He has just begun to walk and imitates a few words , but doesn't really talk much yet. He cries a lot in this session and so several times Mrs Smith takes Diandra and Paul out of the room. Not many of Paul's or Diandra's sounds are transcribed.
@Types:	long, toyplay, TD
